# Obsidian Brain

> Chat with your Obsidian vault locally. No cloud, no API keys.

**Stack:** Python 3.11 · Ollama · ChromaDB · nomic-embed-text · LLaMA 3 · Typer · Rich

---

## Quick Start

### 1. Install Ollama and pull models

```bash
# Install Ollama: https://ollama.com
ollama pull nomic-embed-text
ollama pull llama3
```

### 2. Clone and set up

```bash
git clone https://github.com/harimsd07/obsidian-brain
cd obsidian-brain

python3.11 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate

pip install -e .
```

### 3. Set your vault path

Edit `brain/config.py`:

```python
VAULT_PATH = Path("~/Documents/Obsidian/MyVault").expanduser()
```

Or use the `BRAIN_VAULT_PATH` environment variable:

```bash
export BRAIN_VAULT_PATH="~/Documents/Obsidian/MyVault"
```

### 4. Run first ingest

```bash
brain ingest
```

### 5. Start file watcher (keep running in background)

```bash
brain watch &
```

---

## Commands

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `brain ingest` | Full vault index (run once on first setup) |
| `brain ingest --force` | Re-index everything even if unchanged |
| `brain watch` | Start file watcher daemon |
| `brain stats` | Show index stats and model availability |
| `brain chat` | Interactive Q&A with your notes *(Phase 3)* |
| `brain summarize --note <path>` | Summarize a note *(Phase 4)* |
| `brain summarize --folder <path>` | Summarize a folder *(Phase 4)* |
| `brain related <note>` | Find related notes *(Phase 5)* |
| `brain tag` | Auto-tag untagged notes *(Phase 6)* |
| `brain digest` | Daily digest of recent notes *(Phase 7)* |

---

## Project Structure

```
obsidian-brain/
├── brain/
│   ├── config.py       # vault path, model names, chunk config
│   ├── utils.py        # markdown parser, frontmatter extractor
│   ├── chunker.py      # heading splitter + token-based chunking
│   ├── db.py           # ChromaDB client wrapper
│   ├── llm.py          # Ollama embed + generate wrapper
│   ├── ingest.py       # full vault ingestion pipeline
│   ├── watcher.py      # watchdog file watcher
│   └── commands/       # chat, summarize, related, tag, digest
├── data/chroma/        # persistent vector DB (gitignored)
├── cli.py              # Typer CLI entry point
├── requirements.txt
└── pyproject.toml
```

---

## Configuration

All config lives in `brain/config.py` or as environment variables:

| Variable | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `BRAIN_VAULT_PATH` | `~/Documents/Obsidian/MyVault` | Path to Obsidian vault |
| `BRAIN_CHROMA_PATH` | `./data/chroma` | ChromaDB storage path |

Model and chunking settings are in `brain/config.py`.

---

*All data stays on your machine. Nothing leaves localhost.*
